                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-212-off1136 t18310407-212-crimeloc1139"></join>. The prisoner is my brother; I went to Liverpool on the 27th of February, and left him living in the house - I am <rs id="t18310407-212-viclabel1140" type="occupation">single</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-212-victim1534 t18310407-212-viclabel1140"></join>; my mother and sisters live with me; he lived with them at that time; when I returned, I found he had absconded, and missed the articles named in the indictment - he had no authority whatever to pawn my property - he got his living by minding my warehouse in August last, but in February I hired a ship to send him abroad.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Have you never sent me to Barker's to pawn property? A. I never had occasion to pawn things, I have always had plenty of money - I know nothing about my mother sending you to pledge for her.</p>
               <p>
            
