                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. I produce a soup ladle, 6 table-spoons, a pair of sugar-tongs, and a pepper-box, pawned by the prisoner on the 1st of March - he said it was for his brother (not the prosecutor); he said his brother had a bill to make up - I knew him well.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310407-212-verdict1141" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310407-212-verdict1141" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18.</p>
               <p>The prosecutor here stated that he had been robbed before by the prisoner, and had equipped him for sea, at an expence of 100l.; that he left the vessel, and, upon promises of amendment, he had been prevailed on to take him into his employ, where he remained until he committed the robbery in question.</p>
